#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.51"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.51:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.51:0.2"
msgid "6. Dukkhavagga"
msgstr "6. Suffering"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.51:0.3"
msgid "51. Parivīmaṃsanasutta"
msgstr "51. A Full Inquiry"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn12.51:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn12.51:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn12.51:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.81"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Kittāvatā nu kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivīmaṃsamāno parivīmaṃseyya sabbaso "
"sammā dukkhakkhayāyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, how do you define a mendicant who is making a full inquiry for "
"the complete ending of suffering?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu "
"vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. Bhagavato "
"sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. "
"Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:2.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn12.51:2.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:3.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu parivīmaṃsamāno parivīmaṃsati:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, take a mendicant who makes a full inquiry:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ kho idaṃ anekavidhaṃ nānappakārakaṃ dukkhaṃ loke uppajjati jarāmaraṇaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘The suffering that arises in the world starting with old age and death "
"takes many and diverse forms."

msgctxt "sn12.51:3.3"
msgid "idaṃ nu kho dukkhaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ kiṃsamudayaṃ kiṃjātikaṃ kiṃpabhavaṃ?"
msgstr "What is the source, origin, birthplace, and root of this suffering?"

msgctxt "sn12.51:3.4"
msgid "Kismiṃ sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, kismiṃ asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hotī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"When what exists do old age and death come to be? When what does not exist "
"do old age and death not come to be?’"

msgctxt "sn12.51:3.5"
msgid "So parivīmaṃsamāno evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "While making a full inquiry they understand:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:3.6"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ kho idaṃ anekavidhaṃ nānappakārakaṃ dukkhaṃ loke uppajjati jarāmaraṇaṃ, "
"idaṃ kho dukkhaṃ jātinidānaṃ jātisamudayaṃ jātijātikaṃ jātippabhavaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘The suffering that arises in the world starting with old age and death "
"takes many and diverse forms. The source of this suffering is rebirth."

msgctxt "sn12.51:3.7"
msgid "Jātiyā sati jarāmaraṇaṃ hoti, jātiyā asati jarāmaraṇaṃ na hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"When rebirth exists, old age and death come to be. When rebirth doesn’t "
"exist, old age and death don’t come to be.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:4.1"
msgid ""
"So jarāmaraṇañca pajānāti, jarāmaraṇasamudayañca pajānāti, "
"jarāmaraṇanirodhañca pajānāti, yā ca jarāmaraṇanirodhasāruppagāminī paṭipadā "
"tañca pajānāti, tathā paṭipanno ca hoti anudhammacārī;"
msgstr ""
"They understand old age and death, their origin, their cessation, and the "
"appropriate practice for their cessation. And they practice in line with "
"that path."

msgctxt "sn12.51:4.2"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya paṭipanno "
"jarāmaraṇanirodhāya."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who is practicing for the complete ending of "
"suffering, for the cessation of old age and death."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:5.1"
msgid "Athāparaṃ parivīmaṃsamāno parivīmaṃsati:"
msgstr "Then they inquire further:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘jāti panāyaṃ kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā, kismiṃ sati jāti "
"hoti, kismiṃ asati jāti na hotī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘But what is the source of this rebirth? When what exists does rebirth come "
"to be? And when what does not exist does rebirth not come to be?’"

msgctxt "sn12.51:5.3"
msgid "So parivīmaṃsamāno evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "While making a full inquiry they understand:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:5.4"
msgid "‘jāti bhavanidānā bhavasamudayā bhavajātikā bhavappabhavā;"
msgstr "‘Continued existence is the source of rebirth."

msgctxt "sn12.51:5.5"
msgid "bhave sati jāti hoti, bhave asati jāti na hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"When continued existence exists, rebirth comes to be. When continued "
"existence does not exist, rebirth doesn’t come to be.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:6.1"
msgid ""
"So jātiñca pajānāti, jātisamudayañca pajānāti, jātinirodhañca pajānāti, yā "
"ca jātinirodhasāruppagāminī paṭipadā tañca pajānāti, tathā paṭipanno ca hoti "
"anudhammacārī;"
msgstr ""
"They understand rebirth, its origin, its cessation, and the appropriate "
"practice for its cessation. And they practice in line with that path."

msgctxt "sn12.51:6.2"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya paṭipanno "
"jātinirodhāya."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who is practicing for the complete ending of "
"suffering, for the cessation of rebirth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.82"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:7.1"
msgid "Athāparaṃ parivīmaṃsamāno parivīmaṃsati:"
msgstr "Then they inquire further:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.2"
msgid "‘bhavo panāyaṃ kiṃnidāno … pe …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this continued existence? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.3"
msgid "upādānaṃ panidaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this grasping? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.4"
msgid "taṇhā panāyaṃ kiṃnidānā …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this craving? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.5"
msgid "vedanā …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this feeling? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.6"
msgid "phasso …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this contact? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.7"
msgid "saḷāyatanaṃ panidaṃ kiṃnidānaṃ …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of these six sense fields? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.8"
msgid "nāmarūpaṃ panidaṃ …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this name and form? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.9"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ panidaṃ …"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of this consciousness? …’ …"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.10"
msgid "saṅkhārā panime kiṃnidānā kiṃsamudayā kiṃjātikā kiṃpabhavā;"
msgstr "‘But what is the source of these choices?"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.11"
msgid "kismiṃ sati saṅkhārā honti, kismiṃ asati saṅkhārā na hontī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"When what exists do choices come to be? When what does not exist do choices "
"not come to be?’"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.12"
msgid "So parivīmaṃsamāno evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr "While making a full inquiry they understand:"

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.13"
msgid "‘saṅkhārā avijjānidānā avijjāsamudayā avijjājātikā avijjāpabhavā;"
msgstr "‘Ignorance is the source of choices."

msgctxt "sn12.51:7.14"
msgid "avijjāya sati saṅkhārā honti, avijjāya asati saṅkhārā na hontī’ti."
msgstr ""
"When ignorance exists, choices come to be. When ignorance does not exist, "
"choices don’t come to be.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:8.1"
msgid ""
"So saṅkhāre ca pajānāti, saṅkhārasamudayañca pajānāti, saṅkhāranirodhañca "
"pajānāti, yā ca saṅkhāranirodhasāruppagāminī paṭipadā tañca pajānāti, tathā "
"paṭipanno ca hoti anudhammacārī;"
msgstr ""
"They understand choices, their origin, their cessation, and the appropriate "
"practice for their cessation. And they practice in line with that path."

msgctxt "sn12.51:8.2"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sabbaso sammā dukkhakkhayāya paṭipanno "
"saṅkhāranirodhāya."
msgstr ""
"This is called a mendicant who is practicing for the complete ending of "
"suffering, for the cessation of choices."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:9.1"
msgid ""
"Avijjāgato yaṃ, bhikkhave, purisapuggalo puññañce saṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, "
"puññūpagaṃ hoti viññāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If an ignorant individual makes a good choice, their consciousness enters a "
"good realm."

msgctxt "sn12.51:9.2"
msgid "Apuññañce saṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, apuññūpagaṃ hoti viññāṇaṃ."
msgstr "If they make a bad choice, their consciousness enters a bad realm."

msgctxt "sn12.51:9.3"
msgid "Āneñjañce saṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti āneñjūpagaṃ hoti viññāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they make an imperturbable choice, their consciousness enters an "
"imperturbable realm."

msgctxt "sn12.51:9.4"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno avijjā pahīnā hoti vijjā uppannā, so "
"avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā neva puññābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti na "
"apuññābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti na āneñjābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has given up ignorance and given rise to knowledge, they "
"don’t make a good choice, a bad choice, or an imperturbable choice."

msgctxt "sn12.51:9.5"
msgid "Anabhisaṅkharonto anabhisañcetayanto na kiñci loke upādiyati; "
msgstr "Not choosing or intending, they don’t grasp at anything in the world. "

msgctxt "sn12.51:9.6"
msgid "anupādiyaṃ na paritassati, aparitassaṃ paccattaññeva parinibbāyati."
msgstr ""
"Not grasping, they’re not anxious. Not being anxious, they personally become "
"extinguished."

msgctxt "sn12.51:9.7"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:10.1"
msgid ""
"So sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, sā aniccāti pajānāti, anajjhositāti pajānāti, "
"anabhinanditāti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"If they feel a pleasant feeling, they understand that it’s impermanent, that "
"they’re not attached to it, and that they don’t take pleasure in it."

msgctxt "sn12.51:10.2"
msgid ""
"Dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, sā aniccāti pajānāti, anajjhositāti pajānāti, "
"anabhinanditāti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"If they feel a painful feeling, they understand that it’s impermanent, that "
"they’re not attached to it, and that they don’t take pleasure in it."

msgctxt "sn12.51:10.3"
msgid ""
"Adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, sā aniccāti pajānāti, anajjhositāti "
"pajānāti, anabhinanditāti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"If they feel a neutral feeling, they understand that it’s impermanent, that "
"they’re not attached to it, and that they don’t take pleasure in it."

#. VAR: visaṃyutto naṃ → taṃ vedanaṃ (bj, pts1-2) | vedanaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn12.51:10.4"
msgid "So sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaṃyutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a pleasant feeling, they feel it detached."

msgctxt "sn12.51:10.5"
msgid "Dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaṃyutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a painful feeling, they feel it detached."

msgctxt "sn12.51:10.6"
msgid "Adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaṃyutto naṃ vedayati."
msgstr "If they feel a neutral feeling, they feel it detached."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.83"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:11.1"
msgid ""
"So kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmīti "
"pajānāti, jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ "
"vedayāmīti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"Feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of "
"the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life approaching, they understand: "
"‘I feel the end of life approaching.’"

msgctxt "sn12.51:11.2"
msgid ""
"Kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni "
"sītībhavissanti, sarīrāni avasissantīti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, "
"everything that’s felt, since I no longer take pleasure in it, will become "
"cool right here. Only bodily remains will be left.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. VAR: paṭisisseyya → paṭiviseyya (bj) | patiṭṭhapeyya (s1-3, km, pts1-2) | paṭiseveyya (ṭīkā)
msgctxt "sn12.51:12.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso kumbhakārapākā uṇhaṃ kumbhaṃ uddharitvā same "
"bhūmibhāge paṭisisseyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a person were to remove a hot clay pot from a potter’s kiln and "
"place it down on level ground."

msgctxt "sn12.51:12.2"
msgid "Tatra yāyaṃ usmā sā tattheva vūpasameyya, kapallāni avasisseyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Its heat would dissipate right there, and the shards would be left behind."

msgctxt "sn12.51:12.3"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno "
"kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmīti pajānāti, jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ "
"vedayamāno jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmīti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, feeling the end of the body approaching, they understand: ‘"
"I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of life "
"approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’"

msgctxt "sn12.51:12.4"
msgid ""
"Kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni "
"sītībhavissanti, sarīrāni avasissantīti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life has come to an end, "
"everything that’s felt, since I no longer take pleasure in it, will become "
"cool right here. Only bodily remains will be left.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:13.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn12.51:13.2"
msgid ""
"api nu kho khīṇāsavo bhikkhu puññābhisaṅkhāraṃ vā abhisaṅkhareyya "
"apuññābhisaṅkhāraṃ vā abhisaṅkhareyya āneñjābhisaṅkhāraṃ vā "
"abhisaṅkhareyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would a mendicant who has ended the defilements still make good choices, bad "
"choices, or imperturbable choices?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:13.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:14.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana saṅkhāresu asati, saṅkhāranirodhā api nu kho viññāṇaṃ "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And when there are no choices at all, with the cessation of choices, would "
"consciousness still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:14.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana viññāṇe asati, viññāṇanirodhā api nu kho nāmarūpaṃ "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And when there’s no consciousness at all, would name and form still be "
"found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:15.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:16.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana nāmarūpe asati, nāmarūpanirodhā api nu kho saḷāyatanaṃ "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And when there are no name and form at all, would the six sense fields "
"still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:16.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:17.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana saḷāyatane asati, saḷāyatananirodhā api nu kho phasso "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And when there are no six sense fields at all, would contact still be "
"found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:17.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli2.84"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:18.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana phasse asati, phassanirodhā api nu kho vedanā paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr "“And when there’s no contact at all, would feeling still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:18.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:19.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana vedanāya asati, vedanānirodhā api nu kho taṇhā "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr "“And when there’s no feeling at all, would craving still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:19.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana taṇhāya asati, taṇhānirodhā api nu kho upādānaṃ "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr "“And when there’s no craving at all, would grasping still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:20.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:21.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana upādāne asati, upādānanirodhā api nu kho bhavo "
"paññāyethā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“And when there’s no grasping at all, would continued existence still be "
"found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:21.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:22.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana bhave asati, bhavanirodhā api nu kho jāti paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And when there’s no continued existence at all, would rebirth still be "
"found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:22.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:23.1"
msgid ""
"“Sabbaso vā pana jātiyā asati, jātinirodhā api nu kho jarāmaraṇaṃ "
"paññāyethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“And when there’s no rebirth at all, would old age and death still be found?”"

msgctxt "sn12.51:23.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.51:24.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, bhikkhave, evametaṃ, bhikkhave, netaṃ aññathā."
msgstr "“Good, good, mendicants! That’s how it is, not otherwise."

msgctxt "sn12.51:24.2"
msgid ""
"Saddahatha me taṃ, bhikkhave, adhimuccatha, nikkaṅkhā ettha hotha "
"nibbicikicchā."
msgstr ""
"Trust me on this, mendicants; be convinced. Have no doubts or uncertainties "
"in this matter."

msgctxt "sn12.51:24.3"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassā”ti."
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.51:24.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
